profile_positions.description:
I provided consultancy services to British Council (Nigeria) on the  causes of increasing conflict in Kaduna State in Nigeria. My key responsibilities and achievements: 

•Provided evidence-based data on the current drivers of conflict in Kaduna State and characterised the key actors involved; 
•Analysed the responses of communities and institutions and how those responses have negatively or positively impacted intergroup relations, conflicts and insecurity;
•Investigated the extent to which responses by the state have impacted intergroup relations, conflict and insecurity;
•Evaluated the responses of external actors, such as development partners, international non-governmental organisations and civil society organisations, and determined how such responses impacted intergroup relations, conflicts and insecurity; and
•Suggested strategic interventions and approaches to be adopted to support peaceful and harmonious communities.

Kaduna State is one of the 36 States in Nigeria and the epic-centre of violent extremism and ethno-religious conflict. As the Special Adviser on Peacebuilding and Conflict Resolution to the Governor of Kaduna State in Northern Nigeria, my responsibilities and achievements included:

Research, Training, Policy Advisory Services, Advocacy and Partnership Engagement 
•Collected, researched, analysed and presented information gathered from diverse sources on matters pertaining to intra- and inter-ethnic conflict, peacebuilding and conflict resolution, terrorism and counterterrorism (CT) within Kaduna state and the wider regional context;
•Prepared high quality written outputs, including briefing notes, concept notes, white papers, project proposals and progress reports;
•Engaged in the training of key stakeholders such as youth, women, traditional rulers and religious leaders in Alternative Dispute Resolution;
•Participated, facilitated and/or provided support at conferences, seminars, workshops, roundtable discussions and other relevant fora on peacebuilding, CT and CVE-related matters in Kaduna State;
•Provided intellectual support to the Office of the Kaduna State Peace Commission.
•Acted as a representative of the Governor at meetings, seminars, conferences, and other events as necessary;
•Advocated for the application of ‘Hybrid Political Orders’ (HPOs) in the Kaduna peacebuilding process;
•Ensured effective coordination between Kaduna Peace Commission (KPC), Kaduna Peace Committees, civil society organizations (CSO) and development donors (e.g. DFID, USAID, UN and World Bank);
•Managed the building of strategic alliances and partnerships, especially with key development donors, think tanks, universities, media and non-governmental organizations.
